{\displaystyle (0.3){\frac {1+beak\ modifier}{1+rainstick\ modifier}}}, where beak modifier and rainstick modifier are both zero without artifacts. Thus, with no artifacts equipped, the chance of receiving Golden Eggs from a drone is (0.3) x (1+0) ÷ (1+0) = 30%.

Technically, the Carved Rainstick reduces your chance of receiving Golden Eggs rather than directly increasing your chance of receiving Bocks. Where the Beak of Midas modifier multiplies against the 0.3 odds (increasing chance of Golden Eggs), the Rainstick modifier divides against the 0.3 odds (reducing the chance of Golden Eggs). To find the chance of receiving Bocks, simply subtract the chance of Golden Eggs from 1 (1 - 30% = 70%).

For example, a Simple (T1) Carved Rainstick claims it will increase the chance of Bocks drones by 20%. In reality, it adds a 20% rainstick modifier to the formula: (0.3) x (1+0) ÷ (1+0.2) = 25% chance of Golden Egg drones. Thus, a Simple (T1) Carved Rainstick will reduce the chance of receiving Golden Eggs drones to 25% - or in other words, increase the chance of receiving Bocks drones to 75% (1 - 25% = 75%). This results in a 7.14% (75% ÷ 70% = +7.14%) increase in Bocks drones, and not the stated 20%.

Legendary Rainsticks (and Legendary Beaks) do not follow the above formula but simply set the probability of receiving Golden Eggs to 0%. If both a Legendary Rainstick and a Legendary Beak are equipped, the Legendary Beak takes precedence.

