Effect Stacking
The following stones stack multiplicatively with themselves (and other Artifact effects). For example, one Eggsquisite Shell Stone gives +8% egg value, and using two would give +16.64% egg value: 1.08 × 1.08 = 1.1664

Dilithium Stone
Life Stone
Lunar Stone
Quantum Stone
Shell Stone
Tachyon Stone
The following stones stack additively. For example, one Eggsquisite Soul Stone gives +10 percentage points to your Soul Egg bonus, and using two would give +20.

Clarity Stone
Soul Stone
Terra Stone
The effect of multiple Prophecy Stones is more nuanced. The bonuses from Prophecy Stones are added together (along with any bonus from the Book of Basan and the Prophecy Bonus epic research). This bonus then contributes to the compounding effect of Eggs of Prophecy, meaning each additional Prophecy Stone has a smaller effect on the total Earning Bonus than the previous one in relative terms, but the overall effect depends on Prophecy Egg}} count (and equipped Book of Basan, which will diminish your returns faster); the rate of diminishing is extremely small regardless, and you can usually view Prophecy Stones as not having diminishing returns without substantial loss of accuracy.

Comparing Earning Stones
So that you can easily tell which stones you should slot to earn the most bocks, here are how the various stones compare when stacked:

Life Stones do not belong here; on an empty farm, they impact your bocks the same way as tachyon stones, but their percentages are strictly worse than tachyon stones across all tiers, and the more chickens you already have, the less the impact of life stones on bocks. Do not use life stones to earn bocks.
