Trivia
It costs Golden Eggs to add a Stone to an Artifact, but it is free to remove the Stone from the Artifact. However, you will have to pay the cost of adding the Stone to the Artifact again if you want to put it back on the Artifact.
The effect of Clarity Stones add to each other, so 2 Clarity Stones allow the host artifact to have a 50% effect on the Enlightenment Egg. Even if there is more than one Eggceptional Clarity Stone, the effects will still add to each other; for example, a Legendary Tier 4 Gusset with 3 Eggceptional Clarity stones will have +300% effectiveness, or +75% hab space.
Warning: The game will let you equip Eggfinity Stones onto an Artifact without a confirmation dialogue; this can result in wasting tens of thousands of Golden Eggs due to simply pressing on the wrong part of the screen.
"Eggfinity Stones" are a parody of "Infinity Stones" - powerful gems with different abilities from the Marvel Universe.
