Eggs of Prophecy (EoP) are one of three types of Mystical Eggs found in Egg, Inc. They first appeared in Version 1.7, and are often referred to as Prophecy Eggs (PE) by the community. In this article, they will be referred to as EoP, but the terms are interchangeable and mean the same thing.

EoP function as a compounding multiplier of your current Soul Eggs, increasing their multiplier by 5% per Egg of Prophecy. This bonus can be enhanced through the Prophecy Bonus epic research. Since the bonus from Eggs of Prophecy is compounding, the multiplier bonus grows very quickly.

Eggs of Prophecy appear as a golden egg inscribed hieroglyphics and a golden gem set in the centre. The first time an Egg of Prophecy is earned, the following explanation appears:
Prophecy Popup

Obtaining
Eggs of Prophecy can be obtained from Contracts, Trophies, Seasonal Rewards, and the Daily Gift Calendar. There are a limited number of Eggs of Prophecy a player can earn - primarily limited by the current number of available contracts.

Most Eggs of Prophecy are earned through contracts - though new contracts significantly reduce the number of EoP released. However, Leggacy EoP contracts - released on Fridays - allow players to "catch up" on old EoP contracts they may have missed. Additionally, with a subscription to Egg, Inc. Ultra, one additional Leggacy contract is released on Friday, further reducing the amount of time required to catch up on old EoP contracts. For a comprehensive list of contracts awarding Eggs of Prophecy, see this master list of contracts.

Trophies are the next most common way to earn Eggs of Prophecy. While the first 30 EoP earned through Trophies are relatively easy to attain, the last 10 EoP earned from the Diamond Enlightenment Egg Trophy can be very difficult to earn. One EoP can be earned per month - up to a max of 24 - through the Daily Gift Calendar.

Seasonal rewards were introduced as a way to earn new Eggs of Prophecy in order to reduce the "catch-up time" for new players.

