View source
The Fuel Tank is a feature introduced in Version 1.21 that allows players to store extra Eggs from their current farm. These stored Eggs can then be used to fuel Spaceships while on other farms.

The Fuel Tank has seven upgrade levels. To upgrade beyond the initial level, players must purchase the Pro Permit. Upgrades cost Golden Eggs and increase both the Fuel Tank's capacity and its maximum output rate of the Tank increase.

Added in Version 1.28, limits for each type of Egg can be set using a slider, which controls the maximum amount of that Egg stored in the Fuel Tank. This allows players to set up refueling strategies (see below). If the slider is adjusted below the current amount for a given Egg type, players will be given the option to either keep or dump the excess Eggs.

Unlike most buildings, the Fuel Tank does not reset upon prestige. It is located to the bottom-right of the launchpad and below the Hall of Artifacts. Levels 0 through 3 have a different visual appearance on the farm. Once the Tank reaches level 3, the appearance does not change.


