Strategy
There are many different strategies depending on how far you are in the game, which spaceships you have unlocked, and how many Earnings Bonus/Soul Eggs}} you currently have.

The basic strategy is to fill the tank with as many eggs as possible - except for the least "desirable" egg type needed, which is first a function of how much your ship needs (you want to use a farm for the highest-quantity egg needed, to use the tank as efficiently as possible) and second of value (lower value eggs take longer to set up a farm for, so it's better to fill your tank with higher-value eggs and sit on a lower-value farm). Then, go to the farm for the egg needed by the ship you're launching you didn't put in the tank. Your tank will use stored eggs from the other farms and fresh eggs from your current farm to meet the ship's requirements.

Example: If you’re launching extended Henerprise ships, you need 1TTachyon Egg}} + 2TDilithium Egg}} + 2TAntimatter Egg}} + 2TDark Matter Egg}}. The simplest approach is to store as many non-Dilithium Egg}} as possible in your tank, because it's tied for highest quantity and wins for lowest value, then switch to the Dilithium Egg}} farm. When you fuel spaceships, the ship will use non-Dilithium Egg}} from the tank and Dilithium Egg}} from your current farm; you'll spend a lot of time on said farm, so you'll have plenty of time to work on it to raise your fueling speed. Then refuel either when you run out of fuel, or if you're paying attention, do it before your final set of missions unless you can send all 3.

Once you can egg dance faster, there's no reason at all to sit still on any given fuel farm: provided your tank can fuel 4 ships, you may as well shift farms mid-mission to refuel your tank while you wait. The reason to use a "strategy" is if egg dancing is difficult for you, such that you need or strongly desire to sit still on a fuel farm for extended periods.

Atreggies Henliner
Most players who need a dedicated fueling strategy are launching multiple extended Atreggies Henliners. The following strategy will assume that you have at least a level 3 Tank, which is the minimum level needed to effectively fuel multiple Henliners.

The extended Atreggies Henliner needs 2TTachyon Egg}} + 6TDilithium Egg}} + 6TAntimatter Egg}} + 6TDark Matter Egg}} Eggs per ship.

