The total GE in your piggy per action would be: (base value formula) * event * level bonus * ULTRA bonus, where (base value formula) are the values/formulae mentioned above, event is the piggy fill event, level bonus is the level bonus, and ULTRA bonus is the ULTRA bonus (25% for Standard, 40% for Pro). Thus, consuming an item at piggy level 14 would give 102 'raw' piggy, if there's a 4x piggy fill at the same time, it would be 408. ULTRA and level bonus apply on top of that value. Buying 1 quantum bulb will always net you a profit, since it costs 10GE and returns 25 GE base value.

Strategy
Note: There are unlimited levels - although the image stops changing after level 7. The strategies below only are intended for people that are willing to spend their real money into the piggy bank.

Keep in mind that you need Golden Egg}}32,022,479 to get all Epic Research plus the Hyperloop and fully upgraded Fuel Tank. 15.3 million of this is from the fuel tank. One way you can maximize your return is to wait until your piggy has enough in it to buy all remaining purchases, then wait for a sale and crack it. If you do this, you will only ever need golden eggs after that for boosts or Artifacts. You should buy this over the other offers such as truckloads, as this is the cheapest and most efficient way to get golden eggs while still paying for them. It is important to know that following the Artifacts Update, Piggy Bank Multiplierx2 and x3 rewards are no longer obtainable through contracts. They have all been retroactively replaced with Artifact Case's, containing a set amount of artifacts based off the 0 star, standard length version of the players highest unlock time rocket at the time of claiming the reward.

No Cap events are events that temporarily remove the cap on the piggy. Since the introduction of ULTRA, they have been only existed as ULTRA exclusive events, and the events themselves have ranged from 30mins - 1 hour.

How to use No Cap events to their fullest potential
Note: This strategy is extremely aggressive and intended for late game players.

Credit to user dodgerflamy (251327551258099712) from the Main Egg, Inc. discord server for this strategy. A link to the original post can be found here.

What you need:

ULTRA subscription (ULTRA Pro when cracking piggy recommended)
Unlimited piggy event
A ton of artifacts
The Prep

The fastest way to getting a 1 billion GE piggy is starting your prep as early as you can. This means:

Do NOT consume any artifacts!! If you do not like your inventory cluttered, you can demote shiny artifacts, but save ALL of your commons.
Send exliners regularly so that you're consistently building up your artifacts, send short hens during dubcap and finish off with dubcap exliners right before dubcap ends.
Do not consume your stone fragments.
This one's a bit tough to do, but try to be available each day when the new daily events drop. The most common time for the unlimited piggy event has been when daily events start on Saturday. Events start at 9AM PST each day. 1st event: 9AM PST for 1 hour, 2nd event: 9AM PST for 1 hour, 3rd event: 3PM PST for 1 hour, 4th event: 9AM PST for 30 minutes, 5th event: 9AM PST for 30minutes
Have Ultra Pro already so that you are not scrambling to buy it during the unlimited piggy. However, if this is not something you are able to do, buy Ultra Pro the day of the event, to make use of the 40% piggy boost.
The Event
You do not have to follow this guide exactly. Keep shiny artifacts you regularly use. Keep at least 1 artifact of each type if you use it regularly.

Rules
Do not demote or consume anything you use regularly or plan to use later on.
Check the duration of the event in game, and budget your time accordingly. Most events have been 1 hour which should be enough time to demote/consume everything, however if the event is 30 minutes long make sure you save some time at the end to consume stone fragments, as that gives the most piggy fill (saving the last 5 minutes of the event for consuming frags should be plenty of time).
Reduce the amount of lag that you will get from demotion/consumption by turning on low performance mode in settings, and also switching to a less GPU intensive shell like "Game Pieces" or "Voxel"
Demote all artifacts (remember rule #1).
Consume these artifacts and stones.
