Earnings Bonus
Main article: Earnings Bonus

Prestiging is the main method of gathering Soul Eggs, one of three mystical eggs in the game. It is a major contributing factor to the player's Earnings Bonus, the % on your prestige screen that influences your ability to generate income on all farms.

Preloads
Beyond the first 50 SE, different prestige strategies exist. However, a general rule of thumb is, if the game is slowing down and you have no goals that require staying on the current egg, then it's time to prestige.

The percentage gain of SE compared to your total becomes lower with each prestige. There are several ways to counteract the diminishing returns, such as focusing on finishing Epic Research (especially Soul Food and Prophecy Bonus) and performing multistiges.

Be sure to read through the list of abbreviations before looking at the more advanced strategies below.

A common prestige strategy that is very powerful up into the hundreds of quintillions of EB is called 'single prestige preloading', 'singlestige preloading', or simply 'preloading'.

Standard Permit Simple Guide
This is an extremely simple guide for early game prestiges, intended to be understandable by anyone, no matter what stage they are in the game.

Go to your highest value egg you have unlocked on your farm
Make sure your population is high. Leave space to run chickens!
Use a soul beaconLegendary Soul Beacon}} and a bird feed Jimbo's Best Bird Feed}} to increase your earnings
Run chickens across the screen while boosts are running
Make sure to keep buying research while you are running chickens
When the boosts are completely finished, hit the prestige button! Remember - always prestige before running another set of boosts.
General Preload Guide
Build up to Universe egg (or your highest egg) and buy the best habs and transport vehicles you can afford. Max all research, leaving a level of either Grav Plating or Wormhole dampening not researched (this is to allow running chickens during the boost period)
Activate any artifacts with dilithium stones in them, and then activate one Legendary Tachyon PrismLegendary Tachyon Prism}} (1000x for 10 minutes) and one Epic Boost Beacon Epic Boost Beacon}}(10x for 10 minutes). Instantly switch out your dilithium stone artifacts for your best chalice, best monocle and any other artifact filled with life stones)
Close app and wait for boost period to end. This should net you 8-11B+ chickens.
Once internal hatchery boosts are expired (or when your habs are full), open app and finish any remaining research and make sure transport is sufficient. Don’t finish the level of hab research until AFTER the prism is no longer active.
Activate any artifacts with dilithium stones in them, activate the boost combination of your choice from the list below and then instantly switch to your best prestige setup. Use CarpetSage’s Smart Assistant to work out your best setup for single prestiges.
Run chickens for the duration of the boosts. (Aim to maintain maximum running chicken bonus at all times).
Prestige and start again! Again, never run multiple sets of boosts before prestiging.
Note: Doing multiple rounds of boosts is a waste of GE. Prestige before boosting again to get the most SE gain!

Single Preloaded Dilithium Prestige (Dili Preload)
Credit to user @yami.rl (274484653702774784) on the Cluckingham Palace co-op group discord server.

How to set it up?

It’s basically the same setup as the basic single preloaded prestige. Therefore you need one of the following boost sets.

Most GE / Least time efficient: 1 10x Boost BeaconLegendary Boost Beacon}} (10mins) for 8KGolden Egg}} and 1 1000x IHR Tachyon PrismLegendary Tachyon Prism}} (10mins) for 12K Golden Egg}}
Most time / Least GE efficient: 1 50x Boost BeaconLegendary Boost Beacon}} (10mins) for 50KGolden Egg}} and 1 1000x IHR Tachyon PrismLegendary Tachyon Prism}} (10mins) for 12K Golden Egg}}
Once you have the boosts ready (not activated yet), start preparing your farm by buying 10 Hyperloop trains (max capacity) and all four habs (Chicken Universe), as well as maxing all CR (common research) except WD (Wormhole Dampening) which you should keep on level 24.

When done, you can now switch to your dilithium set and activate the above mentioned boosts. Let habs fill until full. Now that your habs are full deactivate the boosts (if they are still running) and re-equip your dilithium set to activate the following boosts:

