A key component of multistiges is the Hold to Research Epic Research, as this allows for the rapid purchasing of research. Another key component is the Hyperloop Station, due to the amount of eggs being laid with several billion chickens. Three major multistige key components are:

Setting Dilithium Stones in artifacts with preferably 2 (most epics/some legendaries) or 3 (most legendaries) stone slots, then activating the boosts for a longer duration.
The maximum Dilithium Stone boost duration increase is 2.51817x, or a 10-minute boost becoming 25 minutes and 10.902 seconds. This requires 12 T4 Dilithium Stones slotted into four three-slot legendaries.
If you want to get the most out of your boosts, this strategy can also be used during a Longer Boosts event. Simply max out your Universe farm, equip your dilithium set, farm the first “leg” of your multistige (see below), then upgrade to Enlightenment to pause the boosts. Then, on a Double Prestige event (which usually happens every weekend), prestige from Enlightenment. The boosts will resume and keep their extended time, allowing you to utilize both the Longer Boosts event and the Double Prestige event on the same set of boosts. This can allow for boosts with a base duration of 10 minutes to become up to 50 minutes and 21 seconds, greatly increasing GE efficiency and making the multistige session a lot easier.
'Blindjumping' (upgrading an egg without any chickens or research) as many times as possible while performing actions like running chickens, purchasing research and even another blindjump during the black screen. For example - when you prestige, wait for your soul egg count to appear in purple text under the Edible farm icon. Then, immediately start tapping both where you would open the egg menu (in the top left corner) as well as the place where the “upgrade farm” button would be, alternating as fast as you can. You can even do this multiple times to jump several farms (please note that this technique simply increase the speed with which a player can blind jump to farms — it will not allow them to jump to any farm that they could not otherwise reach). The screen will glitch slightly, but it rarely crashes the game and saves a lot of time in the long run, potentially even allowing for an extra “leg” or two to be added to the multi. You can also rapidly tap in the location of the red chicken-hatching button, giving your chickens a head start from the hatchery while waiting for the farm to load in.
