IHR Multistige Guide
Credit to discord user @mennoo (146707232225099776) on the Main Egg, Inc. discord server. Original post can be found here.

Note: Because Eggs of Truth (EoT) affect IHR (1.01^n where n is the number of eggs of truth from Path of Virtue), as your EoT increases, using an IHR set becomes stronger and stronger. Anecdotally, at 90 TE, with an IHR set and collegtibles that give you a 2x+ multiplier to your base IHR, you will be very close to max population by the time Common Research (CR) is complete.

Assumptions / prerequisites:
You already multiprestige, you know at what population you finish research and at what population you normal prestige
You have a good to very good internal hatchery rate (IHR) artifact set. Personally I advise at least T4C monocle/T4E chalice with T4 life stones/6 additional T4 life stones. The better your set, the more effective this strategy becomes
This strategy has not been tested at the lower side of multi-EBs (exa-zetta). If you struggle with buying enough research on build up eggs without your prestige set, this strategy might be less effective. Also, being able to skip buying habs or vehicles on build up eggs helps
You're a fast clicker
Note: Because Eggs of Truth (EoT) affect IHR (1.01^n where n is the number of eggs of truth from Path of Virtue), as your EoT increases, using an IHR set becomes stronger and stronger. Anecdotally, at 90 TE, with an IHR set and collegtibles that give you a 2x+ multiplier to your base IHR (see calculation below), you will be very close to max population by the time Common Research (CR) is complete. Obviously, if your entire 1 minute offline is at max population, the SE gain is significant.

A critical note - at these higher growth rates, if you can blind run some chickens, select habs, and buy all 4 straight to CU before buying CR or transport, you are optimizing clicks and population growth. Mileage may vary depending on your EB.

Calculations before the run:

First, calculate your IHR multiplier from your IHR set. Example: T4C monocle, T4E chalice, 8 T4 life stones gives a multiplier of 1.2 * 1.35 * 1.04^8 = 2.217. Then, take the population you normally finish research at on universe, and multiply it by the IHR multiplier minus 1. Example: if you finish research at 900m chickens, multiply by 2.217-1: 900 * (2.217-1) = 1095. Rounding up for simplicity, this is 1.1b extra chickens. This means all your legs except the first one need to be 1.1b chickens longer than they are usually. Example: if you normally prestige at 3.8b, you now prestige at 4.9b.

Set up

As usual, make sure you are on universe with maxed research. Make sure you have your IHR set and prestige set saved under artifact sets, preferably in the ones you don't have to scroll for. Equip your dilithium set, start your boosts, equip your prestige set, and off we go

The legs themselves

Prestige at the population you calculated above (unless it's the first leg, then prestige at your "old" normal population). While the chickens are running to the hab on your first build up egg (doesn't matter what it is), equip your IHR set.

Side note: the theoretically best thing to do in terms of switching to IHR set is to go to enlightenment after every leg and switch there. However, it will obviously make your prestige sets take longer, thus making your multis less time efficient.

Then, do any non-universe egg build up as normal. When you reach universe, you do the following:

Buy two habs (you might be able to get away with one still, but it's very stressful and buying two is very fast with MAX button)
Finish all research
Buy just enough shipping for this moment using the MAX buttons
Equip your prestige set using the set activation. (This and the previous step can also be swapped, it's really no difference)
Buy more shipping and habs as necessary.Note that it is NOT worth it to buy shipping before doing research because any gains before you equip your prestige set are meaningless anyway Thanks to @staabmia for suggesting to equip the IHR set while running initial chickens on build up egg rather than at the end of universe
