Research (also known as Upgrades) is a feature in Egg, Inc. which allows you to spend Bocks to upgrade some quality relating to your hatchery, habitats, vehicles, or anything else on the farm. For information on Research for the Path of Virtue, see the Egg of Curiosity page.

Most areas of research offer multiple levels, each one costing more than the previous. An upgrade from Tier 1 doubling egg value plus an upgrade from Tier 2 doubling egg value again will quadruple egg value. Since no upgrades in one tier do the same thing, this effectively means that all research will compound with each other. When the number of upgrades researched hits a certain number, the Research Building changes. Each upgrade or research adds Golden Egg}} 3 or more to the Piggy Bank.

For the first few eggs without soul eggs, you can actually skip research and continuously only make chickens to upgrade your eggs (if you are patient enough), but late in the game you will have to use research to progress further.


