However, while an 8-star Henerprise or Henliner can drop the T4 Light of Eggendil, they will do so extremely rarely.

Henliner vs. Henerprise
If you haven't maxed out Henerprise, just go straight to the Henliner. If you have maxed out the Henerprise, opinions are divided. Current general-ish consensus is to send extended Henliners (exliners), and during double capacity events to send two sets of extended Henerprises (assuming they are of a higher star level than your Henliner).

Although the Henliner has a lower minimum quality than the Henerprise, it has a significantly increased capacity, which means that it is in fact better than the Henerprise when both have the same number of stars due to drops per unit time (drops per day for high quality artifacts is what really matters here). However, a Henliner needs significantly more flight experience than a Henerprise for the same number of stars - in fact, with maxed out research it will still take 13-14 months to reach 8 stars on a Henliner.

Because Henliners have a lower minimum quality than Henerprises, they can drop a wider variety of things. Here are the things an exliner can drop that an exhen can't:

T1 Dilithium Stone (i.e. a fragment), Quality 4.1
T1 Terra Stone (i.e. a fragment), Quality 4.2
T1 Carved Rainstick, Quality 4.2
T1 Life Stone (i.e. a fragment), Quality 4.3
T1 Interstellar Compass, Quality 4.32
