Strategy
Credit goes to discord user @mennoo (146707232225099776) for this guide to getting (almost) all diamond trophies on double boost length event.

Original link to the strategy can be found here, from the main Egg, Inc. discord server.

Prerequisites
Pro permit
Double boost time event is active
Boosts: One supreme tachyon prism (1000x IHR for one hour), two large boost beacon (5x all boosts for one hour), two Jimbo's best bird feed (50x earnings for two hours). Total cost: 70k GE, without buy 5 discount
EB: This depends. If you start around the 10Q to 100Q range with Henerprise level artifacts, you should be able to get the edible diamond trophy. However, using this strategy earlier to do the higher value eggs is very feasible as well. This will also depend on your artifacts as well. Also see the "starting egg" section below. I wouldn't advice using this strategy below the 10q EB mark or so (this is small q as in quadrillions).
Artifacts: No artifacts are 100% necessary, but it is advised to have at least a T3 gusset. Other very useful artifacts are chalice, monocle, necklace, ankh, cube, and vial. A dilithium stone setup is also very useful.
Artifact Sets
During the strategy you will use three artifact sets:

Dilithium set: your best set of slotted dilithium stones
IHR set: Your best chalice and monocle. Optionally any artifact with life stones in them
Earnings set: Your best earnings set, probably some combination of necklace, ankh, vial, bob, and monocle. You can use a cube when buying research
Figuring out your starting egg
Depending on your EB and artifacts, you might not be able to start with the edible diamond trophy immediately. However, as you gain PE from the other diamond trophies, your EB will increase, which might tip you over the edge to be able to do edible as well. I would advice to start at the tachyon egg to get an idea of how easy that specific diamond trophy is. If you notice you can do it very easily, you can go to a quite low level egg like medical or rocket fuel. From here on you can go forwards in eggs only, which is easier than prestiging every time.

If you notice tachyon is already quite close, you can go back less far, like quantum or CRISPR for example, and go forwards from there. Once you're back at tachyon, you can decide to just continue with the non-PE trophies, or go back to a lower level egg to try with the newly gained PE.

Figuring out your needed WD level
Chart for figuring out your needed WD level. Includes all gussets and all possible rarities.
Chart for figuring out your needed WD level. Includes all gussets and all possible rarities.

Make sure you know which level of wormhole dampening you need to get 10B hab space when using your best gusset. A chart has been placed at the side.

Calculating your offline IHR
Make sure you know what your internal hatchery rate (IHR) is when having all common IHR research bought and have your IHR artifact set active. Use this to calculate the chickens you gain per minute, when offline, with the boost set active. For example, if your IHR set consists of a 30% chalice and a 15% monocle, and your internal hatchery calm ER is maxed, your offline IHR will be equal to:

7440 (base IHR with all common research) * 3 (IHC effect) * 4 (number of habs) * 1.3 (chalice) * 1.15 (monocle) * 1000 (tachyon boost) * 10 (boost beacon) = 1.335 billion chickens per minute.

The Run Itself
Go to your starting egg. Build up until you start reaching the point of it being hard to buy more research. Equip your dilithium artifact set and activate your boost set.
Activate your earnings artifact set, and buy as much research as you can with your increased earnings. Focus especially on IHR research. Once you have Neural Linking maxed, you can go off-farm. If you notice you cannot max it, that isn't an issue; just go offline when it's clear you won't get any more levels within a reasonable time.
Equip your IHR artifact set. Go off farm for so many minutes that you get +- 5 billion chickens. You can calculate this time using the offline IHR you calculated before; simply divide 5 billion by the offline IHR. On lower level eggs, you can come back a bit earlier, so you have more time to run chickens and earn enough bocks.
Go back online and equip your earnings artifacts set. Run chickens and buy research until you have bought the necessary wormhole dampening level you need. Equip your gusset and IHR artifact set, and go back offline
Stay offline for so many minutes that you get to 10 billion chickens. The exact amount depends on your offline IHR, and your population when you went offline. You can calculate on the fly or do a rough estimate.
Go back online. If everything went well, you should now have 10 billion chickens. Wait until the trophy pops up and claim it. Don't go to the next egg before you claimed the trophy, as you won't get it!
Go to the next egg you want to do, and repeat steps 2 until 6
Note
You can also employ a slightly different strategy. Instead of first going off farm until +-5b chickens, you can also immediately get both the required WD and as many NL levels as possible, and then go off farm only once. This will also give you more time to get the cash for WD, although it could be a slightly less efficient use of the time on your tachyon prisms
Some experiences with this guide can be found here and here (both links require one to be a member of the main Egg, Inc. discord server.)

